{"key":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01|Job|40","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","chapter":40,"textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024","parserRevision":"v11","verses":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:40:1","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":40,"verse":1,"text":"The Lord answered Job:","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:40:2","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":40,"verse":2,"text":"Will the one who contends with the Almighty correct him? Let him who argues with God give an answer.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:40:3","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":40,"verse":3,"text":"Then Job answered the Lord:","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:40:4","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":40,"verse":4,"text":"I am so insignificant. How can I answer you? I place my hand over my mouth.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:40:5","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":40,"verse":5,"text":"I have spoken once, and I will not reply; twice, but now I can add nothing.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:40:6","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":40,"verse":6,"text":"Then the Lord answered Job from the whirlwind:","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:40:7","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":40,"verse":7,"text":"Get ready to answer me like a man; when I question you, you will inform me.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:40:8","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":40,"verse":8,"text":"Would you really challenge my justice? Would you declare me guilty to justify yourself?","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:40:9","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":40,"verse":9,"text":"Do you have an arm like God’s? Can you thunder with a voice like his?","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:40:10","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":40,"verse":10,"text":"Adorn yourself with majesty and splendor, and clothe yourself with honor and glory.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:40:11","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":40,"verse":11,"text":"Pour out your raging anger; look on every proud person and humiliate him.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:40:12","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":40,"verse":12,"text":"Look on every proud person and humble him; trample the wicked where they stand.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:40:13","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":40,"verse":13,"text":"Hide them together in the dust; imprison them in the grave.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:40:14","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":40,"verse":14,"text":"Then I will confess to you that your own right hand can deliver you.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:40:15","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":40,"verse":15,"text":"Look at Behemoth, which I made along with you. He eats grass like cattle.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:40:16","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":40,"verse":16,"text":"Look at the strength of his back and the power in the muscles of his belly.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:40:17","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":40,"verse":17,"text":"He stiffens his tail like a cedar tree; the tendons of his thighs are woven firmly together.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:40:18","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":40,"verse":18,"text":"His bones are bronze tubes; his limbs are like iron rods.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:40:19","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":40,"verse":19,"text":"He is the foremost of God’s works; only his Maker can draw the sword against him.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:40:20","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":40,"verse":20,"text":"The hills yield food for him, while all sorts of wild animals play there.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:40:21","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":40,"verse":21,"text":"He lies under the lotus plants, hiding in the protection of marshy reeds.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:40:22","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":40,"verse":22,"text":"Lotus plants cover him with their shade; the willows by the brook surround him.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:40:23","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":40,"verse":23,"text":"Though the river rages, Behemoth is unafraid; he remains confident, even if the Jordan surges up to his mouth.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:40:24","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17